# Coding Style

- Use TypeScript everywhere.
- Use functional React components.
- Use clear, descriptive naming for components, props, and types.
- Keep functions and components focused on one job.
- Prefer readability over cleverness.
- Keep files reasonably small.
- Avoid unnecessary comments — comment **why**, not **what**.
- Prefer reusable props over duplicated code.
- Avoid clever abstractions too early.
- Prefer readable code over premature optimization.

## React Three Fiber

- Keep scene assembly in `components/world/`, not in `App.tsx`.
- Put basic meshes in `components/primitives/`.
- Use TypeScript types for world objects, rooms, walls, doors, furniture, and player behavior.
